Now I am not a sub leecher <3
Sorry again and have a nice day :)

0:00:28.936 --> 0:00:30.242
Can I gave you a hand?

0:00:30.373 --> 0:00:32.114
If I needed a hand,
I'd ask for it...

0:00:32.244 --> 0:00:34.072
Thank you very much.

0:00:57.139 --> 0:00:58.227
There you go, miss.Thanks.

0:01:01.012 --> 0:01:03.275
Marion.
How's it going?

0:01:03.406 --> 0:01:05.886
Eh. Could be worse.
Brain's still working.

0:01:06.017 --> 0:01:08.367
Is it a pastrami day?

0:01:08.498 --> 0:01:11.327
Yeah. Uh, one
and a quarter pounds. You got it.

0:01:11.457 --> 0:01:14.112
Not a pound and a half,
you overshot last time.

0:01:14.243 --> 0:01:17.028
Oh.
Sorry 'bout that.

0:01:17.159 --> 0:01:19.291
What do we have here?

0:01:19.422 --> 0:01:22.555
Extra-sharp Wisconsin cheddar.

0:01:22.686 --> 0:01:24.905
"Extra-sharp," hmm?

0:01:28.648 --> 0:01:30.955
Ohh.

0:01:31.086 --> 0:01:33.958
You can keep it, Wisconsin.
Ugh.

0:02:01.290 --> 0:02:03.901
It wasn't like this
when I came before.

0:02:17.044 --> 0:02:18.524
Need some help?

0:02:18.655 --> 0:02:20.613
I'm fine!

0:02:25.314 --> 0:02:27.403
Are you sure
you don't want a push?

0:02:27.533 --> 0:02:29.361
I'm sure.

0:02:34.018 --> 0:02:36.194
What happened to poor Nippy?

0:02:36.325 --> 0:02:40.198
Ah. It was my fault.

0:02:40.329 --> 0:02:42.244
I was driving
with the windows open,

0:02:42.374 --> 0:02:44.333
you know, before all this hit.

0:02:44.463 --> 0:02:46.180
And... I don't know...
Something got into him.

0:02:46.204 --> 0:02:48.250
He saw a cat or something...
But he jumped.

0:02:48.380 --> 0:02:49.599
Oh, no.

0:02:49.729 --> 0:02:50.904
I pulled right over,

0:02:51.035 --> 0:02:52.906
screaming my head off,
"Nippyyyy!"

0:02:53.037 --> 0:02:55.387
Ohh.But... he was gone.

0:02:55.518 --> 0:02:57.433
Oh, that's terrible.

0:02:57.563 --> 0:03:00.044
I hope you find him.

0:03:00.175 --> 0:03:01.350
If you could keep an eye out.

0:03:01.480 --> 0:03:02.829
Yeah, I will.
Sure.

0:03:02.960 --> 0:03:05.615
I-I live right over here
on... on Clementine.

0:03:05.745 --> 0:03:07.225
This is my route.

0:03:07.356 --> 0:03:10.446
When I can get this thing going.

0:03:12.578 --> 0:03:14.972
Maybe just a little push.

0:03:17.061 --> 0:03:18.802
Well, if you're sure
you don't mind.

0:03:18.932 --> 0:03:20.499
Nah.
I'm happy to help.

0:03:31.989 --> 0:03:33.208
Okay.
Throw it in neutral.

0:03:33.338 --> 0:03:36.428
And one, two, three.

0:03:40.084 --> 0:03:40.867
There you go.

0:03:40.998 --> 0:03:43.087
Oh, sorry for the trouble.

0:03:43.218 --> 0:03:45.437
Put it back in drive.
Not at all.

0:03:45.568 --> 0:03:48.266
Have a nice day. Yeah, you too.

0:03:48.397 --> 0:03:49.963
Hope you find Nippy.

0:03:50.094 --> 0:03:52.227
Thank you.

0:03:54.925 --> 0:03:57.841
Ohh.
What in the world?

0:04:08.155 --> 0:04:09.635
How ya doing, Marion?

0:04:09.766 --> 0:04:11.246
Great. Ah, good.

0:04:11.376 --> 0:04:13.335
Are you okay? Oh, yeah.

0:05:29.236 --> 0:05:30.716
Okay, okay, okay.

0:05:30.847 --> 0:05:33.545
Actually,
it's my favorite meal to cook.

0:05:33.676 --> 0:05:36.853
Hmm. I like it. And I think
my secret is...

0:05:36.983 --> 0:05:38.289
Ma?

0:05:38.420 --> 0:05:40.552
In the kitchen, Jeffie!

0:05:40.683 --> 0:05:41.988
I have a little trick.

0:05:42.119 --> 0:05:43.773
I bet it's the same
we do in my family.

0:05:43.903 --> 0:05:45.340
An egg.
I knew it.

0:05:45.470 --> 0:05:47.080
And you really work it in.

0:05:47.211 --> 0:05:48.821
I mean, you got to use
your hands.

0:05:48.952 --> 0:05:50.475
You are speaking my language.

0:05:50.606 --> 0:05:54.087
Do you cook? Uh, just a few favorites,
nothing fancy.

0:05:54.218 --> 0:05:56.394
Yeah, simple's best.
I mean, why fuss?

0:05:56.525 --> 0:06:00.746
Oh. Jeffie, this is Mr. Takavic.

0:06:00.877 --> 0:06:03.749
Oh, please,
Mr. Takavic was my father.

0:06:03.880 --> 0:06:06.752
Call me "Gene."

0:06:06.883 --> 0:06:09.842
Don't worry, hon,
he's not an ax murderer.

0:06:09.973 --> 0:06:13.063
If he was gonna chop me to bits
he'd have done it already.

0:06:13.193 --> 0:06:15.979
Right, Gene?

0:06:17.894 --> 0:06:22.420
Well, don't just stand there
like a bump on a log, join us.

0:06:24.814 --> 0:06:27.686
Sometimes he gets a little
nervous around new people.

0:06:27.817 --> 0:06:29.732
Ma... Well, you do.

0:06:29.862 --> 0:06:31.037
Now come on.

0:06:31.168 --> 0:06:34.171
Grab a glass and sit down.

0:06:45.225 --> 0:06:46.575
Tell him how we met, Gene.

0:06:46.705 --> 0:06:47.706
Oh, yeah.

0:06:47.837 --> 0:06:49.926
Uh, well,
I was looking for Nippy...

0:06:50.056 --> 0:06:51.056
Yeah.
His dog, poor thing.

0:06:51.144 --> 0:06:52.363
Well, he ran away.

0:06:52.494 --> 0:06:54.365
And Gene here
was putting up posters.

0:06:54.496 --> 0:06:56.336
And your mom was on her way back
from Hansen's.

0:06:56.367 --> 0:06:58.630
And my wheels got stuck
in the snow.

0:06:58.761 --> 0:07:00.391
Well, that was before
the whole thing conked out.

0:07:00.415 --> 0:07:03.330
Yeah, but Gene here
saved the day.

0:07:03.461 --> 0:07:06.899
He even fixed my dumb scooter...
With duct tape!

0:07:07.030 --> 0:07:10.250
Ah.

0:07:10.381 --> 0:07:12.035
To Gene. Come on.

0:07:12.165 --> 0:07:13.732
Yeah.Ahh...

0:07:16.692 --> 0:07:19.608
Mm.

0:07:19.738 --> 0:07:24.569
So your mom tells me
you're a cab driver?

0:07:27.267 --> 0:07:30.880
Have you ever driven
anyone famous?

0:07:31.010 --> 0:07:32.272
Oh, he sure did.

0:07:32.403 --> 0:07:33.665
Tell him, Jeffie.

0:07:38.322 --> 0:07:39.845
Sammy Hagar.

0:07:39.976 --> 0:07:41.717
No!
The Red Rocker?!

0:07:41.847 --> 0:07:42.979
Hey, I love him.

0:07:47.026 --> 0:07:48.026
That's it! Hey!

0:07:49.420 --> 0:07:52.336
What was he like?
Big tipper?

0:07:52.467 --> 0:07:54.730
I guess.

0:07:54.860 --> 0:07:56.732
Mm.Oh. You know what?
You stay comfy.

0:07:56.862 --> 0:08:00.039
I will rescue
this beautiful creation.

0:08:01.171 --> 0:08:02.955
Look at that.

0:08:05.088 --> 0:08:06.350
Ta-da!

0:08:06.481 --> 0:08:08.352
Gene's staying for dinner.

0:08:23.715 --> 0:08:25.369
Dude, what the fuck?!

0:08:25.500 --> 0:08:27.042
I know it's awkward, right?

0:08:27.066 --> 0:08:29.634
But you don't have to
call me "dad." Yet.

0:08:29.765 --> 0:08:32.115
I dunno what this is about...
But all I have to do

0:08:32.245 --> 0:08:34.813
is pick up the phone
and it's bye-bye, Saul Goodman.

0:08:34.944 --> 0:08:37.139
Yeah, but you haven't picked up
the phone yet, have you?

0:08:37.163 --> 0:08:39.165
Or tried to strong-arm me
for cash.

0:08:39.296 --> 0:08:41.559
And guess what?
I know why.

0:08:41.690 --> 0:08:44.910
Because reward money,
blackmail...

0:08:45.041 --> 0:08:46.366
That's not gonna
tickle your pickle.

0:08:46.390 --> 0:08:48.348
I know what you really want.

0:08:48.479 --> 0:08:51.700
Oh, yeah?
What's that?

0:08:51.830 --> 0:08:53.919
You want in the game.

0:08:54.050 --> 0:08:57.662
"The game"?
W-What... What game?

0:08:57.706 --> 0:08:59.446
The game.

0:08:59.577 --> 0:09:01.623
The one you've been watching
your entire life.

0:09:01.753 --> 0:09:04.016
You got your nose pressed up
against the glass,

0:09:04.147 --> 0:09:05.975
peerin' in
while the big boys play.

0:09:06.105 --> 0:09:07.454
Man, speak English.

0:09:07.585 --> 0:09:08.910
What the hell
are you talking about?

0:09:08.934 --> 0:09:10.022
The game.

0:09:10.153 --> 0:09:11.458
It's right there...

0:09:11.589 --> 0:09:15.027
You can see it,
but you can't touch it.

0:09:15.158 --> 0:09:19.858
The cars, the clothes, the cash.

0:09:19.989 --> 0:09:22.469
The ladies.

0:09:22.600 --> 0:09:24.994
It's about knowing
all the angles, you know,

0:09:25.124 --> 0:09:28.345
putting it all on the line
and winning big.

0:09:28.475 --> 0:09:30.826
But here you are, Jeffie.

0:09:30.956 --> 0:09:33.611
Standing outside
with the suckers.

0:09:33.742 --> 0:09:36.396
Tryin' to pay off that cab,
sweatin' the bills,

0:09:36.527 --> 0:09:37.963
gettin' older.

0:09:38.094 --> 0:09:41.924
It's so close, but, damn it,
you just can't get in.

0:09:42.054 --> 0:09:44.143
Until now.

0:09:44.274 --> 0:09:46.319
I can make it happen.

0:09:50.802 --> 0:09:53.152
You?

0:09:53.283 --> 0:09:55.415
Saul Goodman.

0:09:58.331 --> 0:09:59.855
So, here's the deal.

0:09:59.985 --> 0:10:01.639
I will show you the game.

0:10:01.770 --> 0:10:03.772
And then we're done.

0:10:31.190 --> 0:10:32.583
Two days.

0:10:32.627 --> 0:10:34.280
Caller thinks
it's brother-in-law

0:10:34.324 --> 0:10:36.282
with history of violence.

0:10:36.326 --> 0:10:37.544
10-4.

0:10:47.250 --> 0:10:49.208
Noise complaint.
50 or so teens.

0:10:49.252 --> 0:10:50.819
Parents possibly out of town.

0:10:50.862 --> 0:10:52.462
Neighbors say
this is not the first time.

0:10:53.822 --> 0:10:56.128
Man #3:10-20?

0:10:56.172 --> 0:10:58.435
37882 Crestview.

0:10:59.654 --> 0:11:01.960
Headed that way.

0:11:02.004 --> 0:11:04.702
Missing juvenile.
Caucasian male.

0:11:04.746 --> 0:11:07.836
6'2", 240 pounds.

0:11:07.879 --> 0:11:11.448
Last seen at gas station
on Kerrywood and Western.

0:11:29.248 --> 0:11:32.643
Parents called?

0:11:32.687 --> 0:11:35.690
Got ahold of Mom.
ETA is 20 minutes.

0:11:45.612 --> 0:11:47.310
Woman #4:10-23.

0:12:31.310 --> 0:12:32.311
G'night, ladies.

0:12:32.442 --> 0:12:33.791
See ya, Gene.Bye.

0:12:33.922 --> 0:12:35.532
Yeah.

0:14:10.409 --> 0:14:11.584
There a problem?

0:14:11.715 --> 0:14:13.412
No, I...
I just came to say thanks.

0:14:13.543 --> 0:14:14.587
Um, I'm Gene.

0:14:14.718 --> 0:14:16.024
From Cinnabon.

0:14:16.154 --> 0:14:18.113
Uh, you called the EMTs for me

0:14:18.243 --> 0:14:21.420
when I... fainted.

0:14:21.551 --> 0:14:23.292
Yeah.
I remember you.

0:14:23.422 --> 0:14:24.728
"Get a lawyer!"

0:14:24.859 --> 0:14:28.036
Nick!
Do I detect Cinnabons?

0:14:28.166 --> 0:14:29.472
Yeah!

0:14:29.602 --> 0:14:31.648
Well, Christ almighty,
get him in here.

0:14:34.477 --> 0:14:36.958
I'm sorry about
the lawyer thing.

0:14:37.088 --> 0:14:38.655
Just slipped out.

0:14:42.093 --> 0:14:43.660
It's a free country.

0:14:55.628 --> 0:14:58.153
Hi.
Uh, Gene Takavic.

0:14:58.283 --> 0:14:59.589
Uh...

0:14:59.719 --> 0:15:02.418
Hey, Gene. I'm Frank.
This is Nick.

0:15:02.548 --> 0:15:05.638
Yeah. Nick here, um,
did me a solid,

0:15:05.769 --> 0:15:07.336
so, uh...

0:15:07.466 --> 0:15:09.425
Well...

0:15:15.474 --> 0:15:18.738
Please...
Enjoy yourselves.

0:15:18.869 --> 0:15:20.479
Well, God bless ya.

0:15:20.610 --> 0:15:21.741
Well, 9:45.

0:15:21.872 --> 0:15:23.152
Nick, you wanna
grab yours to-go?

0:15:23.265 --> 0:15:25.920
Sure.Yeah.
He's gotta check the lot.

0:15:26.050 --> 0:15:27.922
Yeah.

0:15:28.052 --> 0:15:30.315
Thanks.

0:15:30.446 --> 0:15:32.013
Uh...

0:15:32.143 --> 0:15:33.623
You want to take a load off?

0:15:33.753 --> 0:15:36.756
Grab yourself a cup of coffee
if you'd like.

0:15:36.887 --> 0:15:37.757
Yeah.
Yeah?

0:15:37.888 --> 0:15:40.064
Oh.
Okay.

0:15:40.195 --> 0:15:42.066
Ohh.

0:15:43.589 --> 0:15:47.158
I should not be doing this.

0:15:54.383 --> 0:15:57.125
Hey, do me a favor,

0:15:57.255 --> 0:16:00.345
if you were ever to cross paths
with my wife, shh.

0:16:00.476 --> 0:16:01.564
Oh.

0:16:01.694 --> 0:16:04.393
Scout's honor.

0:16:04.523 --> 0:16:07.439
Ahh.
Oh, man.

0:16:07.570 --> 0:16:11.356
I haven't had one of these
in forever.

0:16:11.487 --> 0:16:13.619
Watching my waistline.

0:16:13.750 --> 0:16:16.405
Yeah, but every now
and then... No harm, right?

0:16:18.929 --> 0:16:21.540
Oh, wow.

0:16:23.107 --> 0:16:24.761
Mmm.

0:16:36.294 --> 0:16:39.776
Mmm.
Mm-mm-mmm-mmm-mmm.

0:16:42.866 --> 0:16:45.042
So, did you catch the game
last night?

0:16:46.783 --> 0:16:48.828
The game?

0:16:48.959 --> 0:16:52.658
What the hell is wrong
with those guys?

0:16:52.789 --> 0:16:54.834
I can't even talk about it.

0:16:54.965 --> 0:16:56.271
Mm.

0:16:56.401 --> 0:16:59.274
Really thought
this was the year.

0:16:59.404 --> 0:17:00.623
Yeah, me too.

0:17:00.753 --> 0:17:02.059
Mm.

0:17:02.190 --> 0:17:05.236
You know,
Texas wasn't even ranked.

0:17:05.367 --> 0:17:07.543
I know.

0:17:07.673 --> 0:17:09.849
Play-calling was crazy.

0:17:09.980 --> 0:17:11.199
The worst.

0:17:11.329 --> 0:17:15.159
Three downs to make
a foot and a half?

0:17:15.290 --> 0:17:17.640
How hard can it be?

0:17:17.770 --> 0:17:21.383
Well, you can't win
when Martinez plays like that.

0:17:21.513 --> 0:17:22.819
Martinez.

0:17:22.949 --> 0:17:25.865
I mean, what's up with him?

0:17:25.996 --> 0:17:28.216
You think something's off?

0:17:28.346 --> 0:17:30.261
Maybe.

0:17:30.392 --> 0:17:32.220
Mm.

0:17:32.350 --> 0:17:34.439
Next week, Oklahoma State.

0:17:34.570 --> 0:17:36.920
The Okies.
Huh?

0:17:37.051 --> 0:17:38.443
Uh, that's what we called them.

0:17:38.574 --> 0:17:42.143
You ever done the drive?
Topeka, Wichita... Nice.

0:17:42.186 --> 0:17:44.058
Well, then you haven't done it.

0:17:44.188 --> 0:17:45.494
Can't beat Memorial.

0:17:45.624 --> 0:17:46.624
Damn straight.

0:17:46.669 --> 0:17:47.539
What do you love most?

0:17:47.670 --> 0:17:49.150
Now, that's a tough one.

0:17:49.280 --> 0:17:50.649
You think Weedon'll come through
on his home turf?

0:17:50.673 --> 0:17:52.066
Yeah.
No way!

0:17:52.196 --> 0:17:53.850
With that thumb? Thumb's a dealbreaker.

0:17:53.980 --> 0:17:56.157
I'll tell you something.

0:17:56.287 --> 0:17:59.595
The Cougar helmet
was the thumb-breaker.

0:18:02.032 --> 0:18:04.034
Mmm.
Mm-mm-mmm.

0:18:04.165 --> 0:18:05.862
Delicious.

0:18:05.992 --> 0:18:07.559
Mmm!

0:18:11.128 --> 0:18:13.739
Welp, I should probably
be heading back.

0:18:13.870 --> 0:18:15.263
Well, thanks again.

0:18:15.393 --> 0:18:16.593
Oh, it's the least I could do.

0:18:16.655 --> 0:18:17.655
Have a good one.

0:18:17.700 --> 0:18:19.354
Come back anytime.

0:19:10.361 --> 0:19:12.711
Have a good night,
Gene. Goodnight, Krista.

0:19:12.842 --> 0:19:14.322
Goodnight.Goodnight.

0:19:54.536 --> 0:19:55.667
Frank?

0:19:55.798 --> 0:19:58.017
Gene, Gene,
the Cinnabon machine.

0:19:58.148 --> 0:20:00.455
I could smell ya
coming up the hallway.

0:20:00.585 --> 0:20:02.239
Oh, I get that all the time.

0:20:02.370 --> 0:20:03.980
Here you go, guys.

0:20:04.110 --> 0:20:05.373
Hey, can I...

0:20:05.503 --> 0:20:07.679
Hey, Gene, don't even ask.
Grab a coffee.

0:20:07.810 --> 0:20:09.464
That was one hell
of a game, huh?

0:20:09.594 --> 0:20:11.030
What were you thinking
at halftime?

0:20:11.161 --> 0:20:13.642
Well, uh, I was thinking,

0:20:13.772 --> 0:20:16.384
"Hey, this could, uh...

0:20:16.514 --> 0:20:18.342
This could be a long one."

0:20:18.473 --> 0:20:20.538
And I tell you, you know who
I'm not bitching about today?

0:20:20.562 --> 0:20:23.260
Pelini. Nah.Pelini. That's...
Yeah, the coach.

0:20:23.391 --> 0:20:24.977
You know me.
I go at him when things are bad,

0:20:25.001 --> 0:20:27.177
but when he does something good,
I'm all about it.

0:20:45.064 --> 0:20:46.588
Goodnight, Gene. Goodnight!

0:21:05.259 --> 0:21:06.738
They got him in there
for a reason.

0:21:06.869 --> 0:21:09.263
Mm-mmm-mmm.
Mmm.

0:21:58.834 --> 0:22:00.488
I still got it.

0:22:12.064 --> 0:22:14.763
Mm-mm-mm-mmm-mmm.

0:22:39.353 --> 0:22:40.615
Can I help you, sir?

0:22:40.745 --> 0:22:41.790
Oh, yeah.

0:22:41.920 --> 0:22:42.965
Uh, no thanks.

0:22:43.095 --> 0:22:44.793
I'm just browsing.

0:22:44.923 --> 0:22:46.577
Okay. Yeah.

0:22:56.674 --> 0:23:01.157
4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9...

0:23:04.682 --> 0:23:06.423
14...

0:23:08.556 --> 0:23:12.516
15, 17, 18.

0:23:18.566 --> 0:23:21.395
6, 7, 8, 9, 10.

0:24:05.700 --> 0:24:08.833
2...

0:24:08.964 --> 0:24:11.662
11, 12, 13,

0:24:11.793 --> 0:24:14.317
14, 15.

0:24:14.448 --> 0:24:16.537
Alright. Aaand...

0:24:16.667 --> 0:24:17.842
17 feet.

0:24:17.973 --> 0:24:18.973
Right here.

0:24:28.157 --> 0:24:29.288
Ribbon it off.

0:24:29.419 --> 0:24:30.289
Come on.

0:24:30.420 --> 0:24:32.248
All the way, guys.

0:24:37.427 --> 0:24:38.950
Okay.

0:24:38.994 --> 0:24:41.126
